# Implementation Plan: Date-Only + Daily Limit + Queue Number Booking System

## Summary of Change
Replace the current 30-minute time-slot booking system with a simpler, more realistic OPD-style system:
- **Patient** selects only the date → gets a queue number automatically
- **Doctor/Admin** sets max patients per day per clinic
- **Calendar** shows "X slots remaining" on each date — full dates are greyed out
- **Doctor** assigns an approximate time to the patient after booking
- **Patient dashboard** shows queue number + doctor-assigned time + any comments

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `StartTime` and `EndTime` are currently `[Required]` in both the `Appointment` entity and `CreateAppointmentDto`. These will become **optional/nullable** — existing appointment records in the DB will have NULL for these fields after migration. The migration is **non-destructive** (no data is deleted), but existing records will show no time info.

> [!WARNING]
> This is a **database schema migration** — `EF Core Add-Migration` must be run after backend changes. A migration script will be generated automatically.

